<docbook><section><title>GlossaryEntryComment</title><bridgehead class="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml:h3">Comment</bridgehead>
<para>[1] Comment appears as a parameter in the Administrative Assistant DSN creation wizards and the ODBC Data Sources Administrator.
 In either case, it contains information about the use or purpose of a DSN.
 It has no bearing on the actual connection.</para><para>[2] Comment appears in the Administrative Assistant&#39;s Database Agent Settings Form and Wizard.
 In this instance, it allows you to summarize the use or purpose behind a particular agent configuration stanza.
 However, Comment has no bearing on the actual connection.</para><para>See Also: Description </para></section></docbook>